layout":636},{"p":637,"rs":638,"damage":639},"Three lines of large Greek letters; all are incomplete, but the unjustified left margin suggests a text that was originally centred on the stone",{"_":28,"ana":29,"ref":30},{"ana":510},{"lettering":641,"dimensions":655},[642,643],"Thinly incised broad letters of regular height, without serifs or marked terminations to the strokes. Alpha has straight bar; Beta has closed loops, in the second instance separated from one another. Sigma has parallel top and bottom strokes, the mid-strokes meeting slightly over halfway across.",{"_":644,"ref":645},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                ",[646,647,648,649,650,651,654],{"_":36,"target":37},{"_":39,"target":40},{"_":42,"target":43},{"_":45,"target":46},{"_":72,"target":73},{"_":652,"target":653},"Σ tyoe3.2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-tyoe3.2.html",{"_":105,"target":106},[656,660],{"type":124,"l":657,"from":126,"to":658,"h":659,"unit":127},"Line 1-3","line3","60",{"type":129,"l":130,"from":126,"to":131,"h":589,"unit":127},{"_":662,"notBefore":518,"notAfter":593,"evidence":663},"Letters of the 3rd century BCE; the apparent double kingship reference suggests the Hieronian period","lettering, titulature",[665,666],{"_":138,"type":139,"ref":140},{"_":142,"type":143,"ref":144},[668],[147,148],{"_":241,"role":242,"ref":243},{"_":159,"mainLang":160,"languages":671},[159],{"n":163,"url":673,"height":674,"width":675,"desc":676,"surfaceType":168},"ISic003009_tiled.tif","2844px","3672px","Photo J. Prag 2018",[],[172,172,679,680,681,417,178],"Gentili, 1961, Nuovi elementi di epigrafia siracusana","Manganaro, 1963, Tauromenitana: un calendario romano di Tauromenion","Manganaro, 1965, Ricerche di antichità e di epigrafia siceliote",[183,183,683,684,685,428,189],"CBDGFVEG","NF8RRH7M","RGTHAFKT",[687,688,689,209,17,217,197,198,199,200,198,266,202,160],"isic003009","dedication to damater(?)",{"_":629},{"file":691,"uri":691,"title":692,"status":693,"editionAuthor":11,"type":694,"objectType":695,"material":698,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":699,"handNote":703,"date":752,"places":756,"geo":759,"country":149,"region":150,"settlement":142,"repository":761,"idno":762,"textLang":764,"facsimile":766,"provenance":138,"letterHeights":769,"publications":770,"zotero":774,"keywords":778,"html":267},"ISic003331","The Syracusans honour King Gelon, son of Hieron II",{"_":629},{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},{"_":696,"ana":697,"ref":19},"base","#object.base",{"_":217,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"layout":700},{"p":701,"rs":702,"damage":24},"Three lines of finely carved Greek letters, centred on the stone (line one with short vacats at beginning and end, line 2 fully filling the face of the stone, line 3 centred with substantial vacats before and after.",{"_":28,"ana":29,"ref":30},{"lettering":704,"dimensions":739},[705,706],"Elegant wide and very regular letters with thinly carved strokes. Broken bar alpha; beta with equal sized loops; epsilon with short middle bar; kappa with short arms; mu with vertical first and last, middle strokes to half-height; omicron normally full size but small in line 2 (compression a factor); rho with almost fully rounded eye; sigma with approximately horizontal top and bottom strokes or very slightly open; omega full-size rounded and open with straight feet.",{"_":707,"ref":708},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                 